	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				here's the conclusion i've come to.<BR>
in camping these things a week solid to spawn the king i have looted quite a few of these wonderful little bracelets.  i have found that on average, 1 polished bone bracelet will drop every 2 hours of solid camping the eyes in the throne room.  there are 3 spawn points.  the 2 at the side spawn either an evil eye or a lord.  there are 2 different lords that spawn on either side.  in the week i spent here, i have evoked the presence of lord soptyvr 5 times.  he spawns upon the throne.  never once in approximately 100 hours of solid camping that week did king xorbb spawn, i was severly disappointed.  especially since xorbb drops a staff that procs a level 5 shaman spell:sicken(slime crystal staff), but i was camping him for the alleged ring he drops, which has the same stats as the PBB, but is no drop.  xorbb's spawn if extremely too rare for his drop....but camping the eyes will prove very profitable indeed.  rich cash loots drop from the eyes, and this could definately be considered an enchanter's dream zone.  metal bars, gems, and various research pages drop bountifully in this zone.  also; if you plan to pick up any trade skill....this zone if perfect for pottery and for smithing; kill the muddites...don't spend the money for that stuff at the vendor.<BR>
<BR>
Baalenor Cloudforge<BR>
Remembrance of Honor<BR>
level 31 cleric of Brell Serilis
